2014年6月，[[罗切斯特大学|罗切斯特大学]]医学中心的研究在《[[环境健康展望|环境健康展望]]》期刊上发布，研究發現過早暴露在空氣污染所導致的大腦傷害等同於[[孤獨症|孤獨症]]和[[思覺失調症|思覺失調症]]。研究也显示空气污染会影响[[短期记忆|短期记忆]]、[[学习|学习]]能力和[[冲动性|冲动性]]。研究员<u>狄波拉·柯里-施乐塔</u>教授称：“当我们仔细观察[[脑室|脑室]]後发现到，环绕脑室的[[白质|白质]]並没有完全发育。这似乎是因为[[發炎|發炎]]损害了[[脑细胞|脑细胞]]且阻礙了該腦區的成長，[[脑室|脑室]]则干脆膨胀来填充空间。我们的研究也发现有关身体發育的证据，即空气污染与[[孤独症|孤独症]]以及其他{{tsl|en|neurodevelopmental disorders |腦神經發育相關的疾病}}有关。<!--以及其它神经紊乱问题。-->”
另外，研究也發現空气污染对男性的负面影响比女性更大。<ref name="Allen Liu Pelkowski Palmer p. ">{{cite journal | last=Allen | first=Joshua L. | last2=Liu | first2=Xiufang | last3=Pelkowski | first3=Sean | last4=Palmer | first4=Brian | last5=Conrad | first5=Katherine | last6=Oberdörster | first6=Günter | last7=Weston | first7=Douglas | last8=Mayer-Pröschel | first8=Margot | last9=Cory-Slechta | first9=Deborah A. | title=Early Postnatal Exposure to Ultrafine Particulate Matter Air Pollution: Persistent Ventriculomegaly, Neurochemical Disruption, and Glial Activation Preferentially in Male Mice | journal=Environmental Health Perspectives | publisher=Environmental Health Perspectives | date=2014-06-05 | issn=0091-6765 | doi=10.1289/ehp.1307984 | page=}}</ref><ref name=Innes-effects>{{cite news|last1=Innes|first1=Emma|title=Air pollution 'can cause changes in the brain seen in autism and schizophrenia'|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/health/article-2649789/Air-pollution-cause-changes-brain-seen-autism-schizophrenia.html|accessdate=8 June 2014|publisher=Daily Mail|date=6 June 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140608090216/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/health/article-2649789/Air-pollution-cause-changes-brain-seen-autism-schizophrenia.html|archivedate=2014年6月8日}}</ref><ref name=McEnaney-effects>{{cite news|last1=McEnaney|first1=Michael|title=Air pollution link discovered to autism, schizophrenia risks|url=http://www.techtimes.com/articles/8147/20140607/air-pollution-link-discovered-autism-schizophrenia-risks.htm|accessdate=8 June 2014|date=7 June 2014|ref=Tech Times|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140609021844/http://www.techtimes.com/articles/8147/20140607/air-pollution-link-discovered-autism-schizophrenia-risks.htm|archivedate=2014年6月9日}}</ref><ref name="University of Rochester">{{cite news|title=New Evidence Links Air Pollution to Autism, Schizophrenia|url=http://www.urmc.rochester.edu/news/story/index.cfm?id=4100|accessdate=8 June 2014|publisher=University of Rochester Medical Center|date=6 June 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140609164507/http://www.urmc.rochester.edu/news/story/index.cfm?id=4100|archivedate=2014年6月9日}}</ref>

《[[Proceedings_of_the_National_Academy_of_Sciences|美国国家科学院期刊]]》中的研究發現，空氣汙染會增加罹患[[阿茲海默症|阿茲海默症]]或其他型式之[[失智症|失智症]]的風險；在[[神經心理學|神經心理學]]方面則會增加罹患[[憂鬱症|憂鬱症]]的風險。許多文獻也表明，空氣汙染對於學生的[[認知功能|認知能力]]有負面的影響<ref name="BBC News 2018"/>。許多空氣中的汙染物會同時夾帶有毒物質進入一些通道到達人腦進而改變腦中的[[神經化學|神經化學]]。研究指出，空氣汙染與較低的認知功能測驗成績[[相關_(概率論)|相關]]（特別是教育程度較低且性別為男性的受試者），但空氣汙染與較低的認知功能測驗成績並非[[因果關係|因果關係]]。研究人員說，「長期暴露於空氣汙染中」之所以對於教育程度較低且性別為男性的受試者的影響較大的原因之一可能是這些受試者有較高的比例職業為從事戶外勞動（力）的工作。<ref name="BBC News 2018">{{cite web | title=Air pollution 'harms mental performance' | website=BBC News | date=2018-08-28 | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-45326598 | access-date=2018-09-02 | archive-date=2021-04-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210412122038/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-45326598 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Zhang Chen Zhang 2018 p. ">{{cite journal | last=Zhang | first=Xin | last2=Chen | first2=Xi | last3=Zhang | first3=Xiaobo | title=The impact of exposure to air pollution on cognitive performance | journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences | date=2018-08-22 | issn=0027-8424 | pmid=30150383 | doi=10.1073/pnas.1809474115 | url=http://www.pnas.org/content/early/2018/08/21/1809474115 | access-date=2018-09-02 | page= | archive-date=2018-10-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181016131701/http://www.pnas.org/content/early/2018/08/21/1809474115 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="BBC News 中文 2018">{{cite web | title=中国空气污染：可能增加老年痴呆症風險 | website=BBC News 中文 | date=2018-08-28 | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/zhongwen/simp/chinese-news-45331590 | language=zh | access-date=2018-09-02}}</ref>

===相对“干净”地区===
即便某些地区空气污染水平相对较低，公共健康依然会受到严重影响，这是因为吸入的人多。2005年不列颠哥伦比亚肺协会科学研究显示，2010年空气质量进步一小步(PM2.5和臭氧浓度减少1%)会使得温哥华市区增加2900万美元年存款。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bc.lung.ca/pdf/health_and_air_quality_2005.pdf|title=2005 BC Lung Association report on the valuation of health impacts from air quality in the Lower Fraser Valley airshed|format=PDF|date=|accessdate=2010-08-29|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110515185052/http://www.bc.lung.ca/pdf/health_and_air_quality_2005.pdf|archivedate=2011-05-15}}</ref>这项发现是根据健康评估中致命和非致命影响得出的。

=== 生態系統 ===
煙塵等粒子覆蓋植物的葉片，阻礙植物吸收陽光，因此降低[[光合作用|光合作用]]的效率。[[二氧化硫|二氧化硫]]、[[二氧化氮|二氧化氮]]溶於空氣中的水份，形成'''[[酸雨|酸雨]]、酸霧、酸雪，或直接溶於水體（湖泊、溪澗）'''，降低水土酸鹼度，使植物和水中生物死亡。[[二氧化硫|二氧化硫]]能直接殺死[[地衣|地衣]]。空气污染导致全球增溫、臭氧耗損、破壞生態系統。

2014年，印度报道空气污染导致农作物歉收，2010年污染最严重的地方与1980年水平相比减产过半。<ref>[http://www.theguardian.com/environment/2014/nov/03/india-air-pollution-cutting-crop-yields-by-almost-half India air pollution 'cutting crop yields by almost half'] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150406064731/http://www.theguardian.com/environment/2014/nov/03/india-air-pollution-cutting-crop-yields-by-almost-half |date=2015-04-06 }} The Guardian, 3 November 2014</ref>

=== 社會 ===
空气污染导致的[[酸雨|酸雨]]侵蝕金屬及大理石建築、雕像，毀壞戶外文物、藝術品。降低[[土壤|土壤]]酸鹼度，降低農產品收成。光化學煙霧降低能見度，影響旅遊業及對空中[[交通|交通]]造成危險。因空氣[[污染|污染]]而致病的人口造成[[醫療|醫療]]負擔。令能見度下降，遊客減少，經濟倒退。

空气污染一般集中在人口密集的大都市里，特别是在缺乏环境监管或疏于管理的发展中国家。<ref>{{Cite journal | pages = 170–177 | last1 = Ostachuk| first1 = A. | last2 = Evelson | first2 = P. | last3 = Martin | first3 = S. | last4 = Dawidowski | first4 = L. | last5 = Yakisich | first5 = J.S. |last6 = Tasat | first6 = D.R. | title = Age-related lung cell response to urban Buenos Aires air particle soluble fraction | volume = 107 | issue = 2 | journal = Environmental Research | year = 2008 | doi=10.1016/j.envres.2008.01.007}}</ref>然而，即便在发达国家里，人口密集地区污染也达到了臭不可闻的地步，如洛杉矶和罗马就是两个例子。<ref>{{Cite journal | pmc = 1757645 |jstor=27730990 | pages = 605–610 | last1 = Michelozzi | first1 = P. | last2 = Forastiere | first2 = F. | last3 = Fusco | first3 = D. | last4 = Perucci | first4 = C. A. | last5 = Ostro | first5 = B. | last6 = Ancona | first6 = C. | last7 = Pallotti | first7 = G. | title = Air Pollution and Daily Mortality in Rome, Italy | volume = 55 | issue = 9 | journal = Occupational and Environmental Medicine | year = 1998 | pmid = 9861182 | doi=10.1136/oem.55.9.605}}</ref>在2002年和2011年，北京肺癌发病率翻了将近一番。虽然吸烟依然是中国肺癌的首要致因，但吸烟人数正在下降，而肺癌人数却依然上升。<ref>The Daily Telegraph 8 January 2014 'Air pollution killing up to 500,000 Chinese each year, admits former health minister'.</ref>

世界上最严重的短期市民污染事件为印度1984年[[博帕尔事件|博帕尔事件]]。<ref>{{cite news | publisher = [[Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation|Australian Broadcasting Corporation]] | author = Simi Chakrabarti | url = http://www.abc.net.au/worldtoday/content/2004/s1257352.htm | title = 20th anniversary of world's worst industrial disaster | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080118084326/http://www.abc.net.au/worldtoday/content/2004/s1257352.htm | archivedate = 2008-01-18 }}</ref>氰化物从美国联合碳化物工厂泄漏出来，瞬间奪走了25,000人的命，受伤人数在150,000到600,000人左右。英国最严重的空气污染事件是[[1952年伦敦烟雾事件|1952年伦敦烟雾事件]]。在6天中，超过4,000毙命，近期评估的数据则为接近12,000人。<ref name="EHP_112_1">{{cite journal | last1 = Bell | first1 = Michelle L. | author2 = Michelle L. Bell | author3 = Devra L. Davis | author4 = Tony Fletcher | date = January 2004 | title = A Retrospective Assessment of Mortality from the London Smog Episode of 1952: The Role of Influenza and Pollution | journal = [[環境健康視角|Environmental Health Perspectives]] | volume = 112 | issue = 1 | pages = 6–8 | doi = 10.1289/ehp.6539 | url = http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1241789 | pmid = 14698923 | pmc = 1241789 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161230210423/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1241789/ | archivedate = 2016-12-30 }}</ref>前苏联靠近[[叶卡捷琳堡|叶卡捷琳堡]]的[[生物武器|生物武器]]实验室在1979年发生[[炭疽病|炭疽病]]泄漏，即[[斯維爾德洛夫斯克炭疽洩漏事件|斯維爾德洛夫斯克炭疽洩漏事件]]，导致至少64人死亡。<ref>{{cite journal |author=Meselson M, Guillemin J, Hugh-Jones M, et al. |title=The Sverdlovsk anthrax outbreak of 1979 |journal=Science |volume=266 |issue=5188 |pages=1202–8 |date=November 1994 |pmid=7973702 |doi=10.1126/science.7973702 |url=http://www.anthrax.osd.mil/documents/library/Sverdlovsk.pdf |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060921004004/http://www.anthrax.osd.mil/documents/library/Sverdlovsk.pdf |archivedate=2006-09-21 }}</ref>最严重的单次污染事件为1948年10月美国宾夕法尼亚州多诺拉镇事故，导致20人死亡，超过7,000人受伤。<ref>{{cite book | author=Davis, Devra | title=When Smoke Ran Like Water: Tales of Environmental Deception and the Battle Against Pollution| url=https://archive.org/details/whensmokeranlike00davi |publisher=Basic Books|year=2002|isbn=0-465-01521-2}}</ref>

